				\begin{document}$$a_i$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M18"><mml:msub><mml:mi>a</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11229_2016_1268_Article_IEq9.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> votes that the hypothesis is false.</p><p id="Par12">Next, we make two assumptions: First, we assume that the votes are independent, given the truth or falsity of the hypothesis, i.e.<disp-formula id="Equ1"><label>1</label><graphic xlink:href="11229_2016_1268_Equ1_HTML.gif" position="anchor"/></disp-formula>Second, we assume that each group member <inline-formula id="IEq10"><alternatives><tex-math id="M19">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
