				\begin{document}$$c_i^{(k)}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M192"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>c</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>k</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11229_2016_1268_Article_IEq91.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> in round <italic>k</italic> increases linearly as a function of the number of rounds until a maximum value <inline-formula id="IEq92"><alternatives><tex-math id="M193">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
