				\begin{document}$$x&#x0003e;1$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M412"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>x</mml:mi><mml:mo>&#x0003e;</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11229_2016_1268_Article_IEq201.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, by the argument in the proof of Theorem <xref ref-type="sec" rid="FPar1">1</xref>, if the majority of the group members start by voting incorrectly we have that <inline-formula id="IEq202"><alternatives><tex-math id="M413">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
